  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in Senate", 
    "date": "2019-09-18T04:00:00Z", 
    "text": "Pell Grant Restoration Act of 2019\n\n This bill restores a student's Pell Grant eligibility for any period of time during which the student qualified for, or would have qualified for, federal student loan forgiveness due to school closure, assertion of a defense against repayment, or institutional fraud or misconduct.\n\nSpecifically, this bill provides that Pell Grants received by a student during that period of time do not count toward the student's lifetime Pell Grant eligibility period (currently 12 full-time semesters)."
  }, 
